<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1106,1635]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1106,1131]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Morphology.</emphasis>
Crown nearly as long as distance between eyes (
<figureCitation box="[896,962,1106,1131]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1045,1067]" captionTargetBox="[210,1378,190,996]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[188,1398,163,1024]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Cortona silvai sp. n. male: A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376442/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
A). Male anteclypeus nearly parallel-sided (
<figureCitation box="[159,226,1142,1167]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1045,1067]" captionTargetBox="[210,1378,190,996]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[188,1398,163,1024]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Cortona silvai sp. n. male: A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376442/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
C).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1106,1635]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,379,1178,1203]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Subgenital plate long, lateral margin slightly concave (
<figureCitation box="[1017,1087,1178,1203]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1470,1492]" captionTargetBox="[216,1379,220,1421]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[188,1398,193,1449]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Cortona silvai sp. n. A, male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B, male pygofer and segments X – XI, dorsal view; C, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; D, style, dorsal view; E, F, connective and aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376443/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
C). Style with articulating arm long; preapical lobe rectangle; apophysis very short, laterally curved (
<figureCitation box="[952,1022,1214,1239]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1470,1492]" captionTargetBox="[216,1379,220,1421]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[188,1398,193,1449]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Cortona silvai sp. n. A, male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B, male pygofer and segments X – XI, dorsal view; C, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; D, style, dorsal view; E, F, connective and aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376443/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
D). Connective as long as aedeagus. Aedeagus not bifid apically, a pair of long subbasal appendages directed apicad on the dorsal surface (
<figureCitation box="[1295,1361,1250,1275]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1470,1492]" captionTargetBox="[216,1379,220,1421]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[188,1398,193,1449]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Cortona silvai sp. n. A, male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B, male pygofer and segments X – XI, dorsal view; C, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; D, style, dorsal view; E, F, connective and aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376443/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
E–F).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1106,1635]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,411,1286,1311]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Female abdomen.</emphasis>
Sternite VII with median lobe very narrow and digitiform, darkly pigmented in distal twothirds (
<figureCitation box="[230,309,1322,1347]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1279,1301]" captionTargetBox="[208,1368,205,1232]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[188,1398,193,1258]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 11. Females of Cortona: A – D, Cortona minuta: A, first valvula; B, detail of first valvula apex; C, second valvula; D, third valvula. E – I, abdominal sternite VII: E, C. minuta; F, C. catanachae; G, C. silvai; H, C. otamendiensis; I, C. concordica." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376448/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
G).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
