<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="365" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1106,1635]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1538,1563]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is readily distinguishable from all others within 
<taxonomicName box="[1001,1094,1539,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cortona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1001,1094,1539,1562]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Cortona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the aedeagus with the apex tubular rather than cleft and with a pair of robust appendages arising near the midlength of the shaft and directed posterolaterad (
<figureCitation box="[325,390,1610,1635]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1470,1492]" captionTargetBox="[216,1379,220,1421]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[188,1398,193,1449]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Cortona silvai sp. n. A, male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B, male pygofer and segments X – XI, dorsal view; C, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; D, style, dorsal view; E, F, connective and aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376443/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
E–F)
</paragraph>
